Types of graphs: Dense graph: A graph where the number of edges is close to the maximal number of edges possible in the graph. |E| = theta(n^2)
Sparse graph: A graph where the number of edges is close to the minimal number of edges possible. |E| = O(n)
Expander graph: For every set of vertices S with S <= n/2, adding the set of neighbors of vertices in S to S will increase the size of the set by at least some c|S|.
Eigenvectors: For eigenvectors v1, v2, and eigenvalues a1, a2, a1 != a2, v1 will be orthogonal to v2.
